PARITY()

Returns whether the number of set bits is odd.


Syntax

PARITY(Xbit value)

Returns
1bit

Examples

PAIRTY(1011)

Result:
1

PAIRTY(1110)

Result:
1

PAIRTY(1010)

Result:
0


---
REVERSE(Xbit) -> Xbit

Bit reversal

Examples

REVERSE(0011)

Result:
1100

REVERSE(001)

Result:
100
---

CNTONE(Xbit) -> Ybit
Counts how many bits are set.

Example:
CNTONE(00101010)

Result:
11
#3 bits with 1
---

CNTZERO(Xbit) ->  Ybit
Counts how many bits are not set.

Example:
CNTZERO(0101010)

Result: 
100 
#4 bits with 0
---

SIZE(Xbit) -> Ybit

Example:
SIZE(0101010)

Result:
111
# 0101010 has 7bits length doesnt matter the value it has => 7 => 111
---

LROTATE(Xbit data, Ybit count)
RROTATE(Xbit data, Ybit count)

Rotate left/right Y values with not changing the length X of the given value 

LROTATE(1011, 1) returns 0111
LROTATE(1011, 01) returns 0111
LROTATE(1011, 10) returns 1100
LROTATE(1011, 010) returns 1100

